# GAUSS - docker installation

Complete build of GAUSS application through docker installation for test purpose

## Building docker file
	
Building the docker file should be done once. It supposes that you have [docker](https://www.docker.com/docker.io) installed on your system 

	export GAUSS_SRC=/Users/jrom/Devel/gauss
	cd ${GAUSS_SRC}/docker
	docker build -t gauss --force-rm .

## Install and test GAUSS

### Install GAUSS within docker image

First launch gauss image

	export GAUSS_SRC=/Users/jrom/Devel/gauss
	docker run -v ${GAUSS_SRC}:/gauss --rm -ti gauss /bin/bash

Within the docker image, launch the following

	export GAUSS_HOME=/gauss
	cd $GAUSS_HOME

	# Initialize database
	service postgresql-9.5 initdb

	# Local connection to db without password
	cat <<EOF > /var/lib/pgsql/9.5/data/pg_hba.conf
	local   all             all                                     trust
	host    all             all             127.0.0.1/32            trust
	host    all             all             ::1/128                 trust
	EOF

	# Start postgres service
	service postgresql-9.5 start
	

